    "body": "## Summary\n\nTwo fixes for EPLB + NVFP4 quantization on FlashInfer modular kernels (CuteDSL/CUTLASS/TRTLLM):\n\n1. **Exclude broadcast activation scales from EPLB**: `w13_input_scale` and `w2_input_scale` are global per-tensor activation scales shared across all experts (created via `.expand()` with stride 0). They are not per-expert weights and must not participate in expert rebalancing.\n2. **Fix stale quant config after EPLB rearrangement**: Absorb `w13_input_scale` and `w2_input_scale` into `layer.w13_weight_scale_2` and `layer.w2_weight_scale_2` respectively.\n3. **Add `process_weights_after_loading` hook**: TRTLLM fuses `a_scale` into `w_scale_2` in-place (baked into shuffled weight format) and registers `g1_scale_c` as a parameter for EPLB sync. Other backends (CuteDSL/CUTLASS) use `g1_alphas` and `a2_gscale` directly from the quant config.\n\n\n## lm_eval accuracy (gsm8k, DeepSeek-R1-0528-FP4-v2, GB200 NVL72)\n\ngsm8k `lm_eval` was run with:\n\n```\n--all2all-backend \"flashinfer_nvlink_one_sided\"\n```\n\nand\n\n```\n--all2all-backend \"deepep_low_latency\"\n```\n\nboth producing values close to:\n\n|Tasks|Version|     Filter     |n-shot|  Metric   |   |Value |   |Stderr|\n|-----|------:|----------------|-----:|-----------|---|-----:|---|-----:|\n|gsm8k|      3|flexible-extract|    10|exact_match|↑  |0.9530|±  |0.0058|\n|     |       |strict-match    |    10|exact_match|↑  |0.9515|±  |0.0059|\n\n\n## Root cause detail\n\n### CUTLASS (CuteDSL)                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  \n                                        \n``` \n  out1[e] = (A_fp4[e] * s_a1[e]) x (W_fp4[e] * s_w1[e])                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              \n  intermediate = silu(out1_gate[e]) * out1_up[e]            \n  result[e] = (intermediate * s_a2[e]) x (W2_fp4[e] * s_w2[e])                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      \n```\n                                                       \n  All scales applied at block granularity within each independent GEMM.\n\n### TRTLLM\n\nThis is a monolithic kernel which computes:\n\n```\n  out1[e] = GEMM(A_fp4[e], W_fp4[e] * s_block[e]) * g1_scale_c[e]\n  intermediate = silu(out1_gate[e]) * out1_up[e]\n  result[e] = GEMM(intermediate_requant_fp4[e], W2_fp4[e] * s_block2[e]) * g2_scale_c[e]\n```\n\n  where `g1_scale_c[e] = (a1_scale * w1_scale) / a2_scale`.\n\n  Scales are per-expert scalars; block scales apply only to weights. SiLU+mul and requantization happen inside the fused kernel between GEMM1 and GEMM2.\n\n## Test plan\n- [x] Verified on GB200 NVL72 with DeepSeek-R1-0528-FP4-v2, wide expert parallelism (DP=32, EP), and EPLB enabled\n- [x] lm_eval gsm8k accuracy matches baseline at step_interval=4 (most aggressive rebalancing)\n- [x] Confirmed accuracy degrades without fix #2 at high rebalancing frequency\n- [ ] Existing CI tests should pass (no functional change for non-EPLB paths)\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
